        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000002814": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000002814",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000002691\">[2]</$link> For ‘snaring from Grendel,’ ‘sorrows at Grendel’s hands’ has been suggested. This gives a parallel to ‘<span class=\"ang\">láðes</span>.’ ‘<span class=\"ang\">Grynna</span>’ may well be gen. pl. of ‘<span class=\"ang\">gyrn</span>,’ by a scribal slip.</div></div></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000002815": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000002815",
