        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003229": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003229",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\"><div class=\"l\">What favors of yore, when he yet was an infant,</div></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003230": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003230",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003231": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003231",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\"><div class=\"l\">We awarded to him for his worship and pleasure.”</div></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003232": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003232",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003233": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003233",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\"><div class=\"l\">Then she turned by the bench where her sons were carousing,</div></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003234": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003234",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\">\n<span class=\"linenum\">65</span>\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003235": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003235",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\"><div class=\"l\">Hrethric and Hrothmund, and the heroes’ offspring,</div></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003236": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003236",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\">\n<span class=\"sidenote\">Beowulf is sitting by the two royal sons.</span>\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003237": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003237",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\"><div class=\"l\">The war-youth together; there the good one was sitting</div></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003238": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003238",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003239": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003239",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\"><div class=\"l\">’Twixt the brothers twain, Beowulf Geatman.</div></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003240": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003240",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003241": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003241",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003242": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003242",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003115\">[1]</$link> For 1130 (1) R. and Gr. suggest ‘<span class=\"ang\">elne unflitme</span>’ as 1098 (1) reads. The latter verse is undisputed; and, for the former, ‘<span class=\"ang\">elne</span>’ would be as possible as ‘<span class=\"ang\">ealles</span>,’ and ‘<span class=\"ang\">unflitme</span>’ is well supported. Accepting ‘<span class=\"ang\">elne unflitme</span>’ for both, I would suggest ‘<i>very peaceably</i>’ for both places: (1) <i>Finn to Hengest very peaceably vowed with oaths</i>, etc. (2) <i>Hengest then still the slaughter-stained winter remained there with Finn very peaceably</i>. The two passages become thus correlatives, the second a sequel of the first. ‘<span class=\"ang\">Elne</span>,’ in the sense of very (<span class=\"ang\">swíðe</span>), needs no argument; and ‘<span class=\"ang\">unflitme</span>’ (from ‘<span class=\"ang\">flítan</span>’) can, it seems to me, be more plausibly rendered ‘peaceful,’ ‘peaceable,’ than ‘contestable,’ or ‘conquerable.’</div></div></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003243": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003243",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003244": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003244",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-0bfa64 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-e8bee0 twpub-b444daeafa3e6711-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"div1 c12\"><div class=\"fit\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003159\">[2]</$link> Some scholars have proposed ‘<span class=\"ang\">roden</span>’; the line would then read: <i>Then the building was reddened, etc.</i>, instead of ‘covered.’ The ‘h’ may have been carried over from the three alliterating ‘h’s.’</div></div></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/b444daeafa3e6711/text/000003245": {
            "role": "text",
